<title>Section Summary</title>
<list id="fs-id1167064818568">
<item>The angle of reflection equals the angle of incidence.</item>
<item>Plane mirrors and convex mirrors reflect virtual, erect images. Concave mirrors reflect light to form real, inverted images or virtual, erect images, depending on the location of the object.</item>
<item>Image distance, height, and other characteristics can be calculated using the lens/mirror equation and the magnification equation.</item>
</list>
</section>

